Package: plausibounds
Title: Plausible Bounds for Treatment Path Estimates
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Ryan",
           family = "Kobler",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "kobleary@gmail.com")
Description: Calculate and visualize plausible bounds as proposed in Freyaldenhoven (2025)
    for dynamic treatment path estimates. Given a treatment path, variance matrix, and significance level, plot various uncertainty measures cleanly with `plausible_bounds()` and `create_plot()`.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5)
